Dog Trainer Questionnaire vs Outcome (Success, Fail)

Marinara Marcato

Introduction

This document tests the hypothesis that there is a difference in behaviours reported in the standardised questionnaire Monash Canine Personality Questionnaire - Revised considering dogs training outcome.

Data Exploration

Data Analysis

Kruskal-Wallis one-way analysis of variance test was used to investigate whether there was a statistically significant difference between the behaviours reported by Trainers and the Training Outcome of the dogs. The variables that showed p_value < 0.05 are below:

##                  Variable    outcome_p
## 1  Motivation.Persevering 4.531845e-02
## 2      Training.Attentive 3.836573e-02
## 3       Training.Obedient 2.194657e-02
## 4       Training.Reliable 4.524963e-04
## 5      Training.Trainable 6.606082e-05
## 6  Amicability.Easy.going 6.875695e-04
## 7     Amicability.Frienly 3.956970e-03
## 8     Amicability.Relaxed 1.193169e-03
## 9    Amicability.Sociable 1.251421e-02
## 10    Neuroticism.Fearful 6.864945e-04
## 11    Neuroticism.Nervous 1.147607e-03
## 12 Neuroticism.Submissive 2.840415e-02
## 13      Neuroticism.Timid 5.829840e-03
